{"key":"post-6773511","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6773511</id>\n<content>Hay is a terrible substrate.&amp;nbsp; Straw is better.&amp;nbsp; Manure is better yet.&amp;nbsp; I've inoculated stuff all over the place.&amp;nbsp; Just take some jars of mycelium and a bag of cow manure from the local nursery.&amp;nbsp; Mix them together and cover with 1/2&quot; of soil.&amp;nbsp; Water with whatever is handy.&amp;nbsp; Stream water, tap water, etc.&amp;nbsp; It need not be sterile because nothing is sterile outdoors.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The grow below is from a few years ago at the local botanical gardens.&amp;nbsp; When I found out they use manure from the mounted police department stables, I couldn't resist visiting after hours with a few jars. &lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/lol.gif&quot; alt=&quot;:lol:&quot; title=&quot;:lol:&quot;/&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/05-38/717919428-IMGA1281aaa.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/05-38/717919428-thumb_IMGA1281aaa.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>6773445</prev>\n<first>6773445</first>\n<last>6773511</last>\n<when>1176273416</when>\n<utime>04/11/07 09:36 AM</utime>\n</post>"}